Class userInterface.GameApplet extends javax.swing.JApplet implements Serializable

engine

GameEngine engine

Class userInterface.GameEngine extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

controller

GameControler controller
The GameControler instance asociated to this GameEngine. The GameController acts as a Control layer between the domain of the game and the external events raised from the GameFrame, GameApplet or the GameEngine itself.

See Also:
GameEngine.addGameController(control.GameControler)

updatables

java.util.ArrayList<E> updatables
An ArrayList containing all the Updatable instances that the GameEngine should update to, at the game updating state stage.

See Also:
Updatable.update(), GameEngine.gameUpdate()

renderables

java.util.ArrayList<E> renderables
An ArrayList containing all the Drawables instances that the GameEngine should render and render to, at the game render and render state stages.

See Also:
Renderable.render(java.awt.Graphics), GameEngine.gameDraw()

updatablesOutDated

boolean updatablesOutDated
This field holds the updatables 'upToDate' state. That means if this field contains a false value, the updatables ArrayList is outdated. This field should not be modified since the GameControler instance will do if it detects that the updatable instances from the GameClient has been changed. At every updating stage the GameEngine instace checks for this field to know if it has to ask for the updated updatables ArrayList to the GameControler.

See Also:
GameEngine.gameUpdate(), GameEngine.setUpdatablesToOutDated(), GameControler.getUpdatables()

renderablesOutDated

boolean renderablesOutDated
This field holds the renderables 'upToDate' state. That means if this field contains a false value, the renderables ArrayList is outdated. This field should not be modified since the GameControler instance will do, if it detects that the renderables instances from the GameClient has been changed. At every drawing stage the GameEngine instace checks for this field to know if it has to ask for the updated renderables ArrayList to the GameControler.

image

java.awt.Image image
The Image Object used to obtain the Graphics object used at the rendering stage. The GameEngine first creates that Image Object with it's width and height values, and latter extracts the Graphics object used to render the renderables to it. At the drawing stage, that Image object will be drawn to the screen by the GameEngine graphics instace, replacing the old one. This technique is called "DoubleBuffering".

See Also:
GameEngine.gameDraw(), GameEngine.gameRender(), Component.createImage(int, int)

graphics

java.awt.Graphics graphics
The Graphics object used to render by the GameEngine

See Also:
GameEngine.gameDraw()

width

int width
The GameEngine's width

See Also:
GameEngine.setWidth(int)

height

int height
The GameEngine's height

See Also:
GameEngine.setHeight(int)

animator

java.lang.Thread animator
This field holds the Thread wich update, render, and render the updatables and renderables instances in a continuous loop. By taking this processes in a separated Thread we'll be able to control the desired FPS and UPS. This technique is known as Active Rendering, since the rendering stage is always 'active'

See Also:
GameEngine.run(), GameEngine.addNotify()

running

boolean running
boolean field that indicates if the animation loop is currently running. If it's value changes to false, the GameEngine will stop.

See Also:
GameEngine.run(), GameEngine.terminate()

fps

int fps
The desired Frames Per Second that the GameEngine instance should accomplish. Obviously, the real FPS obtained will vary on the CPU and GPU demands. The default value is 50 FPS, but this can be changed via the setFps() method

See Also:
GameEngine.setFps(int)

period

long period
The time that the GameEngine should take in a loop to acomplish the desired frames per second. (in milliseconds)

See Also:
GameEngine.updatePeriod(), GameEngine.setFps(int)

numberOfDelaysPerYield

int numberOfDelaysPerYield
This field indicates how many delays the GameEngine will permit before calling Thread.yield() to allow other Threads to be processed (if they need it). A delay is produced when the GameEngine loop doesn't finish within the specified period.

maxFrameSkips

int maxFrameSkips

showingEngineStatus

boolean showingEngineStatus
boolean field to control if the GameEngine status should be rendered and drawn to the screen. (It's useful while the testing and development stages).

See Also:
GameEngine.showEngineStatus(), GameEngine.hideEngineStatus()

timer

JannatonTimer timer
This field holds one of the JannatonTimer instances provided by the timers package. In the current version we provide two implemented timers, the TimerPerf and the TimerNano.

See Also:
TimerPerf, TimerNano

stats

Stats stats
This field holds a reference to the Stats Object wich will perform the necessary operations for showing the GameEngine status, if it's required.

See Also:
GameEngine.showEngineStatus(), GameEngine.hideEngineStatus()

Class userInterface.GameFrame extends javax.swing.JFrame implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

engine

GameEngine engine
The GameEngine instance that will be added as a child to this GameFrame

gameFrameDimension

java.awt.Dimension gameFrameDimension
This field contains the Dimension that the GameFrame will handle when it's in windowed mode.

graphicsDevice

java.awt.GraphicsDevice graphicsDevice
The GraphicsDevice object extracted from the GameFrame GraphicsConfiguration

graphicsConfiguration

java.awt.GraphicsConfiguration graphicsConfiguration
The GraphicsConfiguration object extracted from this GameFrame

avaibleDisplayModes

java.awt.DisplayMode[] avaibleDisplayModes
This field handles an array with the avaible DisplayMode objects on the running windowed system. The setFullScreenDisplayMode() uses this field to ensure that it's able to change to it.

See Also:
GameFrame.setFullScreenDisplayMode(java.awt.DisplayMode)

currentDisplayMode

java.awt.DisplayMode currentDisplayMode
This field references at its initial time to the DisplayMode instance returned from graphicsDevice.getDisplayMode(). Since the GameFrame has had a call to the setFullScreenDisplayMode() method, the field will use to refer to one of the avaible DisplayMode object contained in avaibleDisplayModes array.

See Also:
GameFrame.getDisplayMode(), GameFrame.setFullScreenDisplayMode(java.awt.DisplayMode)

isFullScreenModeSupported

boolean isFullScreenModeSupported
Field used to indicate if the Java Full Screen Exclusive Mode is avaible on this windowing system.

See Also:
GameFrame.setFullScreenON(), GameFrame.setFullScreenOFF()

areDisplayChangesSupported

boolean areDisplayChangesSupported
Field used to indicate if DisplayMode changes are suported on this windowing system.

See Also:
GameFrame.setFullScreenDisplayMode(java.awt.DisplayMode)

isFullScreenModeOn

boolean isFullScreenModeOn
Field used to indicate if this GameFrame instance is running with the Java Full Screen Exclusive Mode enabled. It's default value is false
